âWhat!
the fools have gone and missed him, then!
â
âWell, what of that?
you missed him yourself, did you not?
â
Mocquet shook his head.
âWell, well, thereâs some devilry about this,â he said.
âThat I should miss him was surprising, but it was perhaps possible; but that Moynat should have shot twice and missed him is not possible, no, I say, no.
â
âNevertheless, so it is, my good Mocquet.
â
