â And suiting the action to the word, I set off running.
âStop, stop, do not run, whatever you do,â cried Mocquet, clenching his teeth and stamping.
âWe must go quietly, until we know better what we have to deal with.
â
âWell, we will go quietly, then; but at any rate, let us go!
â
Mocquet then began to follow the wolfâs track, step by step.
âThereâs not much fear of losing it,â I said.
âItâs plain enough.
â
âYes, but thatâs not what I am looking for.
â
âWhat are you looking for, then?
â
âYou will know in a minute or two.
â
The other huntsmen had now joined us, and as they came along after us, the keeper related to them what had taken place.
