â asked Landry.
âPoor boy!
â said the mistress of the mill, with a smile and a pitying movement of the shoulders, which, at any other time, would have made Landry almost die of joy, but, as it was, only doubled his distress.
âPerhaps even now I might have time to hide,â he said.
âHide!
