They were probably poachers he thought, who had reasons like himself for wishing to get inside the park.
There being no longer anything to bar his passage, he had only, as before, to let the horse go its own way, and he accordingly did so.
The horse followed the walls of the park at a quick trot, carefully choosing the soft edge of the road, and not uttering a single neigh; the intelligent animal seemed as if it knew that it must make no sound or at least as little sound as possible.
