Thibault was left free once more, and alone.
His hands however were still bound, and his feet fettered.
First he tried to undo the cord with his teeth, but this he found impossible.
Then he tried to wrench his bonds apart by the power of his muscles, but that too was unavailing; the only result of his efforts was to make the cord cut into his flesh.
It was his turn to bellow with pain and anger.
