Agnelette sighed and shook her head, but made no further resistance; she knew that Engoulevent would not give in on this matter, and she reserved her strength wherewith to renew her entreaties when she was once indoors.
And in truth, the young huntsman only considered that he was doing his duty, for a great _battue_ had been arranged for the next day in a part of the forest on the further side from that on which Agnelette had met Thibault.
Etienne, therefore, was bound to go without delay and report to his master the whereabouts of the Wolf-leader.
