He turned; there was the black wolf himself, creeping noiselessly along, like a dog coming to rejoin its master.
The wolf would have been invisible in the gloom but for the flames shot forth from his eyes, which illuminated the darkness; he went round the hearth and sat down facing the shoe-maker.
